### System information

Godot v4.4.beta4 - Windows 11 (build 26100) - Multi-window, 1 monitor - Vulkan (Forward+) - integrated Intel(R) Arc(TM) Graphics (Intel Corporation; 32.0.101.5768) - Intel(R) Core(TM) Ultra 5 125H (18 threads)

### Issue description

Change a vec2 uniform to instance cause the shader fail to compile.

The shader code itself means nothing, it is simplified from my real project,  tried to make it as simple as possible:

```gdscript
shader_type canvas_item;

instance uniform vec2 change_me = vec2(0.0);

vec4 blend_color(vec2 uv) {
	vec2 pixel = uv + change_me;
	return vec4(1.0);
}

void fragment() {
	COLOR = blend_color(UV);
}
```

### Steps to reproduce

Open the minimal reproduction project, editor will print a long list of error:

