### Issue description

Getting an error when I try to add a TreeItem to the selected TreeItem using C#

### Steps to reproduce

I have a Tree in my scene. In `_Ready()` I do:

```c#
_accountTree = GetNode<Tree>("Tree");

TreeItem rootTreeItem = _accountTree.CreateItem();
rootTreeItem.SetText(0, "Root");

TreeItem treeItem = _accountTree.CreateItem(rootTreeItem);
treeItem.SetText(0, "Child 1");

TreeItem treeItem = _accountTree.CreateItem(rootTreeItem);
treeItem.SetText(0, "Child 2");
```


In the godot editor, I set the Tree node to connect the `item_selected() `signal to the method `_OnTreeItemSelected()`

The want here is when one selects an item in the tree, it adds a child to it.

```c#
public void _OnTreeItemSelected() {
    TreeItem selectedTreeItem = _accountTree.GetSelected();

    TreeItem treeItem = _accountTree.CreateItem(selectedTreeItem);
    treeItem.SetText(0, "Another Child");
```


...

On the SetText line I get the error " Exception of type` 'System.NullReferenceException' was thrown: Object reference not set to an instance of an object."`

Using the debugger I can see that selectedTreeItem is a TreeItem and does seem like it is the correct one (based on the name).

Maybe one shouldn't be able to be able to add a child on the fly like this? Or perhaps that is a good use case but I am just doing it wrong?

